The United States welcomes the decisions made by the United Kingdom and Belgium to authorize military force against ISIL in Iraq. The air forces of these countries will now join the United States, France, and the Iraqi air force in conducting air strikes against ISIL positions. Denmark and the Netherlands have also announced plans to provide fighter aircraft to the coalition. Additionally, Saudi Arabia, Jordan, the United Arab Emirates, Bahrain, and Qatar have decided to participate in airstrikes against ISIL in Syria. These decisions show the international community's commitment to taking action against these terrorists. The United States will continue to work with its international partners to degrade and defeat ISIL.